      "span_text": "Subsequently, we performed complete spinal cord transection at vertebral level S2 in rats, as previously described. rats were subjected to a laminectomy at S2 level but no Sci in sham group and received no treatment in control group. after injury, muscle layers and skin were sutured orderly and rats were injected with 2 ml sterile saline subcutaneously. then the rats were placed into warmed cages with free access to food and water under a standard 12-h/12-h light/dark cycle."
